Cedar Rapids Jefferson taking advantage of Waterloo West mistakes jumped to a 23-0 halftime lead and rolled to a 44-15 victory over the Wahawks. J-Hawks quarterback Jared Eivins threw two touchdown passes to give Jefferson the big first half lead. West High closed the gap to 23-15 in the fourth quarter but the J-Hawks scored 21 unanswered points to snap a two game losing streak and improve to 4-3.
